getting wisdom teeth pulled out i'm usually very hard to frighten about anything but half a year ago i had a crying spell over knowing that my wisdom teeth will be pulled out now it's scheduled for tomorrow and i'm not sure how to feel i'm still very nervous though if anyone has had their wisdom teeth pulled out can you tell me how it went was it painless how much pain was there afterwards and for how long i've heard the actual surgery is usually under minutes also this will be my first time under anesthesia i heard about using no straws why is it bad to use them it's different for everyone but i had mine out with minimal pain the same day only had to take painpills out of an entire bottles worth stuck with mushy food for about a week simply because i was afraid of getting anything stuck where my wisdom teeth were pulled out stock up on some yummy pudding and ice cream ramen noodles soup mashed potatos etc and don't use straws other than that i am sure you will be fine and just take the pain pills if not and oh yeah surgery is really fast i was in and out in an hour and the anesthesia just sort of makes you relaxed and then poof you fall asleep without knowing Local anesthesia Breastfeeding Japanese cuisine Anesthesia Tooth Soup German cuisine Urinary incontinence Coffee Out-of-body experience M*A*S*H (TV series) Barbecue Similarities between the Bible and the Qur'an Shaggy dog story Three Stooges Characters of Naruto Cuisine of the Philippines One Piece minor characters Tofu Pain The Amber Spyglass Breakfast Cocaine Jon Secada Fishing She Loves You Trapping Babe Ruth Fecal incontinence Russian joke Cuisine of Denmark Jewish cuisine Episodes of Lost (Season 1) Tonsillectomy Dental caries Scenes from a Memory Ice cream Little Britain Diazepam Tea Cat Apollo 8 Knots Landing The Shining (film) Medical prescription Nutmeg Hypoglycemia Morphine British cuisine Time Out of Mind Timon and Pumbaa Hip hop collaborations Paget's disease of bone Chronic fatigue syndrome Rice p